step.reason:
\text{For a function to be continuous at a\\
point it's limits on either sides should be equal\\
to the value of f(x) at that point}

step.tex:
\begin{align}
    \lim_{x\to 1^-}f(x) &=1 \\
    \lim_{x\to 1^+}f(x) &=5 \\
    f(1) = 1
\end{align}
\\ \text{Hence, f(x) is discontinuous at x=1.}\\
